# This file defines the available spaCy language models.
# Each line represents a spaCy model with the following columns (tab-separated):
#   <value>           <name>                      <lang>  <size>  <model_name>
#
# - value: Unique identifier for the model (model_name is recommended)
# - name: Display name shown to users
# - lang: Language code (en, es, de, fr, etc.)
# - size: Model size (sm, md, lg, trf)
# - model_name: spaCy model package name (used with spacy.load())
#
# Models must be installed in the Galaxy environment before use.
# Install with: python -m spacy download <model_name>
#
# Example entries (uncomment and ensure models are installed):
#
#en_core_web_sm	English (small)	en	sm	en_core_web_sm
#en_core_web_md	English (medium)	en	md	en_core_web_md
#en_core_web_lg	English (large)	en	lg	en_core_web_lg
#en_core_web_trf	English (transformer)	en	trf	en_core_web_trf
#es_core_news_sm	Spanish (small)	es	sm	es_core_news_sm
#es_core_news_md	Spanish (medium)	es	md	es_core_news_md
#es_core_news_lg	Spanish (large)	es	lg	es_core_news_lg
#de_core_news_sm	German (small)	de	sm	de_core_news_sm
#de_core_news_md	German (medium)	de	md	de_core_news_md
#de_core_news_lg	German (large)	de	lg	de_core_news_lg
#fr_core_news_sm	French (small)	fr	sm	fr_core_news_sm
#fr_core_news_md	French (medium)	fr	md	fr_core_news_md
#fr_core_news_lg	French (large)	fr	lg	fr_core_news_lg
